{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1659/comments/6707302.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:None..None?path=gazebo%2Futil%2FLogRecord.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1659/_/diff#comment-6707302"}}, "parent": {"id": 6703481, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1659/comments/6703481.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1659/_/diff#comment-6703481"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1659, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1659.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1659"}}, "title": "Windows util updates"}, "content": {"raw": "I was thinking along the same lines. We could support `getEnv` that accepts an enum. The enum would then be translated correctly inside the implementation of `getEnv`. My reasoning is that there are likely multiple environment variables that differ between *nix and Windows.\n\nIssue #1601 captures these comments. Add suggestions there.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I was thinking along the same lines. We could support <code>getEnv</code> that accepts an enum. The enum would then be translated correctly inside the implementation of <code>getEnv</code>. My reasoning is that there are likely multiple environment variables that differ between *nix and Windows.</p>\n<p>Issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1601/support-a-cross-platform-getenv\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Support a cross platform `getEnv`\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#1601</a> captures these comments. Add suggestions there.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-05-07T03:23:35.490186+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbuck